**If you're looking for a way to play your own music with crossfade, this is it!  Download My DJ now.  It's free - give it a try!**

App Description:

My DJ creates a continuous stream of your own music.

By default, My DJ will shuffle through your library, smoothly crossfading between each song.  Want more of a "DJ" experience?  Adjust the Song Play Time setting, and My DJ will randomly play sections of each song, crossfading along the way.

There are so many ways to use My DJ!  At any time, if you decide to continue listening to the entire current song, just tap the "Full Song" button. My DJ can be used in this way to scan through your own songs audibly, much like one would scan through the stations of a radio then stop to listen to a whole song!

You'll have fun discovering and tweaking the different settings available in My DJ.

Extra Features Include:
    * Restart Song button
    * Adjustable crossfade
    * Retina display support
    * Choose which songs or playlists to play
    * Works with Multitasking Media Control buttons

New!  Join My DJ's premium monthly subscription:
- Length of Subscription:  1 month
- Price of Subscription:  $0.99 USD Monthly
- This subscription is auto-renewable unless cancelled prior to renewal
- Link to Privacy Policy: http://mydjapp.com/privacy.html

We value our customers' feedback very much.  Many features have been added based on feedback, and we're not done yet.

Download My DJ today and find out what all the craze is about!  You'll never go back to listening to music the OLD way!

results.description:
NetDJ is a way for you to combine your music tastes with friends, tailoring your listening experience to fit everybody in a group. Create networks, invite friends, and add songs you would like to hear, and Net DJ will take care of the rest. Given everybody's song preferences, Net DJ generates songs that represent everybody's interest. How to use it:

1) Create and join networks with people with who you want to share your preferences.

2) Add songs or entire playlists that you want to be heard through this network.

3) Start playing the automatically generated Queue, or customize your queue my manually playing/adding songs.

Note: The Queues are not synchronized. So, while everybody in a network has access to the same pool of songs, each person's queue is independent of others
